questions: Is it a physical/tangible object?
Is it a concept or idea created by humans?
Is it something that occurs naturally in the physical world?
Is it related to living organisms (plants, animals, etc.)?
Is it a category or classification of organisms (like a species, family, or type of organism)?
Is it a relationship or interaction between organisms (like predation, competition, symbiosis, etc.)?
Is it something produced or created by organisms (like a nest, web, etc.)?
Is it a state or condition that organisms can experience (like health, disease, hunger, etc.)?
Is it related to the environment or habitat where organisms live (like a biome, ecosystem, etc.)?
Is it a characteristic or trait possessed by some organisms (like bioluminescence, ability to fly, etc.)?
Is it a part or component of organisms (like DNA, cells, organs, etc.)?
Is it a substance or chemical produced by or found in organisms (like hormones, enzymes, etc.)?
Is it a natural event or phenomenon that affects organisms but isn't inherently biological (like weather, natural disasters, etc.)?
Is it a natural cycle or pattern that involves organisms (like seasons affecting migration, day/night cycles, etc.)?
Is it something related to the very concept of life itself (like consciousness, existence, etc.)?
Is it related to evolution, natural selection, or other mechanisms of how species change over time?
Is it related to the origin or beginning of life on Earth?
Is it related to the communication or signaling between organisms?
Is it related to biodiversity or the collective variety of life forms on Earth?
